- content_for(:title, 'The Cycle')

%table
  %tr
    =render 'cycle', phase: Phase.ep, top: false
    %td 🌕<br /><br /><br />Use
    =render 'cycle', phase: Phase.ej, top: false

  %tr
    %td.left 🌓 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Energy
    %td &orarr;
    %td.right Strength &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 🌗

  %tr
    =render 'cycle', phase: Phase.ip, top: true
    %td.bottom Get<br /><br />💤<br /><br />🌑
    =render 'cycle', phase: Phase.ij, top: true

%p You cannot change the fact that you cycle through all four phases of the cycle. You <em>can</em> change your behaviors to reflect your <em>actual needs</em> instead of your phase-based “shoulds”.
